    "body": "I kind of dislike the proposal \"epoch hour/eHour\" as a physicist, since when two units are combined as a word, it conventionally means they are multiplied (e.g. kilowatt hours). And an epoch is clearly a unit.\r\nSomething more like the \"kibibyte\" approach would be more appropriate. In fact, this is pretty much the same idea of approximating units with powers of two. Suggestions:\r\n\r\n * BiHour, BiDay, BiWeek, ...\r\n * Bour, Bay, Beek, Bonth (B could stand for Binary or Beacon chain)",
