    "updated_at": "2020-06-23T06:56:02Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I would be much less opposed to this if the terms were not cribbed directly from English.  For example, `eears, eonths, eeks, eays, eours, einutes, eeconds` would at least make it abundantly clear to any outside listener/reader that they need to go look up what those terms meant, but would allow for standardized order of magnitude values in communication.  My problem with `eth-month` or `ethereum-month` is that I can almost guarantee that people will shorthand it to `month` and confusion will be introduced.",
